AB  - We bring together here a group of writers, thinkers, clinicians, and expressive artists with training, expertise, and experience in the areas of dance, literature, music, poetry, theater, the visual arts, and psychoanalysis. Together their work captures the essential theme of this issue, bringing together the fields of art and creativity with that of clinical practice. Their work embraces both psychoanalytic and creative expression, and guides us to observe the rich and highly textured fabric that comes from weaving together the domains of psychoanalysis and creativity. Such an interdisciplinary perspective on psychoanalytic engagement enhances our understanding of cross-modal models in therapy. We hope that this inclusive view of the expressive arts and psychoanalysis will further our understanding of what produces change in the analytic encounter while broadening our appreciation of the influences of aesthetic values and creativity. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2023 APA, all rights reserved)
