AB  - 'Hearing by listening', a redundancy used in Spanish, just like 'going down a descent' or 'going in inside'. What are we to hear with if not with our ears? And yet, perhaps it is not all that evident that we listen with our ears, and what if we do so with our eyes? We say that 'we devour someone with our eyes'; perhaps we can also say that 'we hear them with our eyes'-before devouring them. Indeed, sight conditions and transforms hearing. How far does this relationship go? Is it merely a crossmodal experience? Hearing by listening... Is it redundant? And if it were not? And if it happened that often, mechanically, we descend ascents, we go in outside...? (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
